In the induction step, the induction hypothesis says there is a unique n-germ g_{n}\colon s(n)\to X.
    Consider the function g_{s(n)}\colon s(s(n))\to X defined by
           g_{s(n)}(k) =       \begin {cases}         h(g_{n}(n)) & \text {if $k = s(n)$}\\         g_{n}(k) & \text {if $k < s(n)$}       \end {cases}

